---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="FAQ &middot; The Pairing &middot; Caleb Arlow">
  <PageHero eyebrow="Reader questions">
    <Fragment slot="title">FAQ.</Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="lead">
      Common questions about The Pairing: the romance, the age range, the spice level, and the release schedule.
    </Fragment>
  </PageHero>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-text">
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What age is The Pairing for?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>All twelve books are written for ages 14+ (upper YA). The protagonists age across the series (13 in Book One, late teens by the end of the Transformation arc, then a new pair 13-15 in the Legacy arc), but the writing stays YA throughout.</p>
            <p>If you give YA fantasy romance to a 14-year-old reader, you can give them the entire series.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is it spicy?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>No. The Pairing is a slow burn from Book One to Book Twelve. Kisses, longing, secret messages through threads, emotional intimacy, fade-to-black at the furthest. The romance is the engine of the series. It just doesn't get explicit.</p>
            <p>This is for the YA reader who wants the bond without the bedroom door.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Are the books in Kindle Unlimited?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes. Thread of Gold, Thread of Silver, and Thread of White are all available free with Kindle Unlimited. Books 4-12 will also be KU on release.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do I need to read in order?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes. The Pairing is one continuous story across twelve books. The Discovery arc (Books 1-3) reads as a single piece, and each later book picks up where the previous one ended. Start with Thread of Gold.</p>
            <p>If you only want to read the Legacy arc (Books 10-12), you can technically start at Book 10 with a different protagonist (Caleb), but you'll miss the emotional weight of the bond the new generation inherits.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What are the tropes?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Fated bond. Slow burn. Forbidden romance. Color-coded magic system. Found family. Government-controlled love. Forced separation. Surveillance. Resistance. Generational legacy.</p>
            <p>If you've loved <em>Matched</em>, <em>Delirium</em>, <em>Red Queen</em>, or <em>Powerless</em>, the DNA is here.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Are there content warnings?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes. The series includes: state surveillance and authoritarian control, forced separation of romantic partners, on-page death of family members (later arcs), grief, the loss of bodily autonomy as a central theme, and the long aftermath of trauma.</p>
            <p>The romance itself is consensual and age-appropriate throughout. The system the romance exists inside is the antagonist.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How often do new books come out?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Books 1-3 are out now. Book 4 (the first book of the Rebellion arc) is in production. The publishing schedule targets quarterly releases through 2027-2029, with the full series complete by 2030.</p>
            <p>The newsletter is the fastest way to know exact release dates. Cover reveals and pre-order links go there first.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Will there be audiobooks?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Audiobook plans are in development. The newsletter will announce production updates as they happen.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can I share my review or talk about the series online?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Please do. BookTok, Bookstagram, Goodreads, blog reviews, all of it is welcome. Tag <strong>@caleb.arlow</strong> on TikTok, <strong>@calebarlow</strong> on Instagram, and the post might end up on Caleb's profile.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Why doesn't the author show his face?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Caleb Arlow writes under a pseudonym. The work is the work. The romance and the world are what matters. No author photo, no in-person events, no interviews. Email is the channel for everything else.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .faq-list {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }
  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }
  .faq-item summary {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--paper-50);
    padding: var(--s-5) 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--s-4);
    transition: color var(--dur-base) var(--ease-out);
  }
  .faq-item summary:hover { color: var(--thread-gold-2); }
  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq-item summary::after {
    content: '+';
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    color: var(--thread-gold);
    transition: transform var(--dur-base) var(--ease-out);
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after {
    content: '-';
  }
  .faq-body {
    padding: 0 0 var(--s-6) 0;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .faq-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--fg-secondary);
  }
  .faq-body p + p { margin-top: var(--s-3); }
</style>
